{"title_page": "Bethany Hamilton", "text_new": "{{short description|American surfer}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=August 2013}}\n{{Infobox surfer\n| name           = Bethany Hamilton\n| image          = Bethany Hamilton surfing (sq cropped).jpg\n| caption        = Hamilton surfing in September 2016\n| birth_name     = Bethany Meilani Hamilton\n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|mf=yes|1990|2|8}} \n| birth_place    = [[Lihue, Hawaii]], U.S.\n| residence      = [[Kauai, Hawaii]], U.S\n| height         = {{convert|5|ft|11|in|m|abbr=on}}\n| weight         = {{convert|155|lb|kg|abbr=on}}\n| best_year      = 2005 \n| sponsor's       = [[Rip Curl]]\n| major_achievements = [[ESPY Award]] (2004)<br />[[National Scholastic Surfing Association|NSSA]] National Helping Kids Champion (2005)<br />2nd place, [[Association of Surfing Professionals|ASP]] World Junior Championships (2008)\n| website         = {{url|bethanyhamilton.com}}\n| children        = 2\n}}\n\n'''Bethany Meilani Hamilton''' (born February 8, 1990) is an American professional [[surfing|surfer]] who survived a 2003 [[shark attack]] in which her left arm was bitten off but who ultimately returned to [[World Surf League|professional surfing]]. She wrote about her experience in the 2004 autobiography ''Soul Surfer: A True Story of Faith, Family, and Fighting to Get Back on the Board''. In April 2011, the feature film ''[[Soul Surfer (film)|Soul Surfer]]'' was released. She now has a new movie called ''Unstoppable'' where she shows the struggles and happiness of her family. Hamilton has been in the World Surf League for quite a few years.\n\n==Surfing career==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- style=\"background:lime green;\"\n! colspan=\"4;\"  style=\"background:green; color:white; text-align:center;\"| Placings in surf competitions\n|- style=\"background:#bdb76b;\"\n! Year!!Event!!Place!!Country\n|-\n| 1998 || Rell Sun Menehune || 1st|| [[Australia]]\n|-\n| 2002 || Open Women's Division of the [[National Scholastic Surfing Association|NSSA]] ||  1st || [[United States|USA]]\n|-\n| 2004 || NSSA National Competition ||  1st  || Australia\n|-\n| 2005 || NSSA National Competition ||  1st || USA\n|-\n| 2006 || NSSA National Championship: 18-and-under Finalist ||  5th  || USA\n|-\n| 2006 || Hawaii Team Highlights || 4th<br>3th* || USA\n|-\n| 2007 || NSSA Regionals || 1st  || USA\n|-\n| 2007 || T & C  Pipeline Women's Pro ||  1st  || USA\n|-\n| 2008 || US Open of Surfing\u2014[[Huntington Beach, California]] ||  5th  || USA\n|-\n| 2008 || Roxy Pro Surf Festival\u2014[[Phillip Island]] ||  3rd || Australia\n|-\n|2008\n|ASP's World Qualifying Series\n|14th\n|\n|-\n| 2009 || Rio Surf International in [[Rio de Janeiro]] ||  3rd  || [[Brazil]]\n|-\n|2009\n|WSL's World Qualifying Series \n|14th\n|Peru\n|-\n| 2009 || Billabong ASP World Junior Championship  ||  2nd || Australia\n|-\n|2012\n|Rip Curl Cup Padang Padang \n|\n|Indonesia\n|-\n| 2014 || Surf 'n' Sea Pipeline Women's Pro  ||  1st || USA\n|-\n| 2015 || Swatch Women's Pro<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldsurfleague.com/events/2015/wct/1282/swatch-womens-pro/results?resultsType=prizes|title=Prizes & Placing - 2015 Swatch Women's Pro|publisher=}}</ref>  ||  13th || USA \n|-\n| 2016 || Fiji Women's Pro<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldsurfleague.com/events/2016/wct/1440/fiji-womens-pro/results|title=Results - 2016 Fiji Women's Pro|publisher=}}</ref>  ||  3rd || [[Fiji]]\n|}\nShe was the first woman surfer to surf in the Rip Curl Cup in 2012.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://indosurflife.com/2012/07/bethany-hamilton-receives-wildcard-entry-into-rip-curl-padang-cup/|title=Bethany Hamilton receives wildcard entry into Rip Curl Padang Cup|date=2012-07-25|website=IndoSurfLife.com|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-29}}</ref> <!-- \n<nowiki>*</nowiki>4th at Brazil event, 5th at World Games event in the United States.\n-->\n\n==Personal life==\nHamilton was born on February 8, 1990 to Tom and Cheri Hamilton, on the day of a double rainbow.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://bethanyhamilton.com/|title=Bethany Hamilton {{!}} Soul Surfer, Professional Surfer, Role Model, Inspiration|website=Bethany Hamilton|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-29}}</ref> She has two older brothers Noah (born in 1981) and Timothy (born in 1986). She began surfing at the age of 8 and gained her first sponsorship by age 9.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.biography.com/athlete/bethany-hamilton|title=Bethany Hamilton|website=Biography|language=en-us|access-date=2020-02-29}}</ref> Hamilton was home-schooled from 6th grade through high school. She is a Christian.<ref name=\"home-school1\" /> In early 2012 Hamilton met youth minister<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20801085,00.html|title=Bethany Hamilton: My Husband Keeps Me Surfing|last=Dodd|first=Johnny|date=March 28, 2014|work=People|accessdate=March 28, 2014}}</ref> Adam Dirks through mutual friends.<ref name=\"us2013\">{{cite web|url=http://www.usmagazine.com/celebrity-news/news/pro-surfer-bethany-hamilton-marries-adam-dirks-2013188|title=Pro Surfer Bethany Hamilton Marries Adam Dirks|last=Webber|first=Stephanie|date=August 18, 2013|work=Us Weekly|accessdate=August 18, 2013}}</ref> They became engaged in 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.etonline.com/news/133768_Surfer_and_Shark_Attack_Survivor_Bethany_Hamilton_Engaged_to_Adam_Dirks/index.html|title=Surfer Bethany Hamilton Engaged|last=Wicks|first=Krista|date=May 7, 2013|work=Entertainment Tonight|accessdate=May 8, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.gospelherald.com/articles/48397/20130712/soul-surfer-bethany-hamilton-engaged-to-wed-youth-minister-adam-dirks.htm|title=Soul Surfer Bethany Hamilton Engaged to Wed Youth Minister Adam Dirks|date=12 July 2013}}</ref> The couple were married on August 18, 2013 at an estate on [[Kauai]]'s north shore, near where she grew up.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20727275,00.html|title=Bethany Hamilton's Official Wedding Photo|accessdate=June 22, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.gospelherald.com/articles/48646/20130818/soul-surfer-bethany-hamilton-gets-married-to-christian-youth-minister-adam-dirks.htm|title=Soul Surfer Bethany Hamilton Gets Married to Christian Youth Minister Adam Dirks|date=18 August 2013}}</ref> The couple have a son named Tobias, born in 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2015/06/15/bethany-hamilton-baby_n_7588512.html?ncid=txtlnkusaolp00000592|title=Bethany Hamilton Introduces New Baby Boy With Adorable Family Photo|last=Herreria|first=Carla|date=June 15, 2015|work=[[The Huffington Post]]|accessdate=June 15, 2015}}</ref> In 2018 they had a second son, Wesley.<ref>{{cite tweet|user=bethanyhamilton|author=Bethany Hamilton|number=917133168196460544|title=More than thankful to share our joyous news!!! #babyinthere #babyonboard\u2728\ud83c\udf89\u2764\ufe0f|date=October 8, 2017|accessdate=October 8, 2017}}</ref> She also has two shar pei dogs named Hanalei \"Hana\" and Kombucha \"Booch\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://bethanyhamilton.com/|title=Bethany Hamilton {{!}} Soul Surfer, Professional Surfer, Role Model, Inspiration|website=Bethany Hamilton|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-29}}</ref>\n\n==Shark attack and recovery==\nOn October 31, 2003, Hamilton, aged 13 at the time, went for a morning surf along Tunnels Beach, [[Kauai]], with her best friend [[Alana Blanchard]], Alana's father and brother, Holt and Byron, when a {{convert|14|ft|m|adj=mid|-long}} [[tiger shark]] attacked her,<ref>{{cite web |title=About |work=Bethany's General Biography |publisher=BethanyHamilton.com |year=2003 | url=http://www.bethanyhamilton.com/ |accessdate=September 17, 2007}}</ref> severing her left arm just below the shoulder. The Blanchards helped paddle her back to shore, then Alana's father fashioned a [[tourniquet]] out of a rash guard and wrapped it around the stump of her arm. She was rushed to [[Wilcox Health|Wilcox Memorial Hospital]]. By the time she arrived there she had lost over 60% of her blood and was in [[Hypovolemia|hypovolemic shock]]. A doctor living in a hotel nearby raced to the rescue. Her father, who was scheduled to have knee surgery that same morning, was already there, but she took his place in the operating room. During subsequent media interviews, she confirmed that she felt normal when she was bitten and did not feel much pain from the bite at the moment of the disaster, but felt numb on the way to the hospital.\n[[file:Bethany Hamilton 20070311.jpg|thumb|Hamilton surfing in March 2007]]\n\nWhen the news broke out of the shark attack, a family of fishermen led by Ralph Young presented to investigators photos of a {{convert|14|ft|m|adj=mid|-long}} tiger shark they had caught and killed about one mile from the attack site. It had surfboard debris in its mouth. When measurements of its mouth were compared with those of Hamilton's broken board, it matched. In late 2004, the police officially confirmed that it was the same one that had attacked her.\n\nDespite the trauma of the incident, Hamilton was determined to return to surfing.<ref name=\"home-school1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.home-school.com/Articles/soul-surfer.php|title=Homeschool World - Articles - Soul Survivor: The Bethany Hamilton Story - Practical Homeschooling Magazine|publisher=Home-school.com|date=2003-10-31|accessdate=2014-04-28}}</ref> One month after the attack, she returned to her board.<ref>{{cite web|last=Clark |first=Mark |title=Soul Surfer Interview With Bethany Hamilton! |url=http://whatculture.com/film/soul-surfer-interview-with-bethany-hamilton.php |work=WhatCulture! |accessdate=December 15, 2012 |date=September 24, 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131029204455/http://whatculture.com/film/soul-surfer-interview-with-bethany-hamilton.php |archivedate=October 29, 2013 |df=mdy }}</ref>\n\nInitially, she adopted a custom-made board that was longer and slightly thicker than standard and had a handle for her right arm, making it easier to paddle, and she learned to kick more to make up for the loss of her left arm. After teaching herself to surf with one arm, she returned to surfing on November 26, 2003, just 26 days after the attack and entered her first major competition on January 10, 2004.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://bethanyhamilton.com/|title=Bethany Hamilton {{!}} Soul Surfer, Professional Surfer, Role Model, Inspiration|website=Bethany Hamilton|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-29}}</ref> She now uses standard competitive performance short-boards.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://theinjuryco-op.com/bethany-hamilton-amputee-surfer/#.U17YSfldWT8 |title=Bethany Hamilton \u2013 Amputee Surfer &#124; The Injury Cooperative|publisher=Theinjuryco-op.com|accessdate=2014-04-28}}</ref> The shark-bitten surfboard that Hamilton was riding during the attack, as well as the bathing suit she was wearing at the time, a gift from ocean photographer [[Aaron Chang]], are on display at the [[California Surf Museum]] in [[Oceanside, California]].<ref>{{cite web|author=Guy Bagley|url=http://surfmuseum.org/surfmuseumexhibits.html|title=Current Exhibits|publisher=Surfmuseum.org|accessdate=August 19, 2013|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130806070345/http://surfmuseum.org/surfmuseumexhibits.html|archivedate=August 6, 2013|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"CSM\">Museum Exhibit (Permanent Exhibit). [http://surfmuseum.org/bethany-hamilton-courageous-inspiration/ \"Courageous Inspiration: Bethany Hamilton\"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160914180722/http://surfmuseum.org/bethany-hamilton-courageous-inspiration/ |date=September 14, 2016 }} ''California Surf Museum''. Retrieved 6 September 2016.</ref>\n\n==Media==\nSince the attack she has appeared as a guest on numerous television shows. Her manager, Roy \"Dutch\" Hofstetter, who went on to produce the film ''[[Soul Surfer (film)|Soul Surfer]]'', managed her rise through the media from shark attack victim to inspirational role model. The television shows she has appeared on include ''[[The Biggest Loser]]'', ''[[20/20 (U.S. TV series)|20/20]]'', ''[[Good Morning America]]'', ''[[Inside Edition]]'', ''[[The Oprah Winfrey Show]]'', ''[[The Ellen DeGeneres Show]]'', ''[[Today (U.S. TV program)|The Today Show]]'', ''[[The Tonight Show]]'' and ''[[Dude Perfect]]'', as well as in the magazines ''[[People (magazine)|People]]'', ''[[Time (magazine)|Time]]'', and ''[[American Girl (magazine)|American Girl]]''. Additionally she was the cover story in the first issue of ''[[NiNe. magazine|niNe]]'' magazine.<ref>[http://thegardenisland.com/news/article_15d110c8-4bc0-5459-b4db-dbd8c506752a.html \"Shark attack survivor discusses products and jewelry lines in new mag\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160411132331/http://thegardenisland.com/news/article_15d110c8-4bc0-5459-b4db-dbd8c506752a.html |date=April 11, 2016 }} by Lanaly Cabali, [http://thegardenisland.com The Garden Island], June 30, 2006.</ref>\n\nShe has participated in multiple public speaking events and is \"motivating audiences worldwide to live their life with more tenacity, courage, and faith\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://bethanyhamilton.com/|title=Bethany Hamilton {{!}} Soul Surfer, Professional Surfer, Role Model, Inspiration|website=Bethany Hamilton|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-29}}</ref>\n\nIn 2004 she won the [[ESPY Award]] for [[Best Comeback Athlete ESPY Award|Best Comeback Athlete]]<ref>{{cite web|title=The 2004 ESPY Awards winners|url=http://espn.go.com/espy2004/s/04nomineesindex.html|publisher=ESPN|accessdate=December 15, 2012}}</ref>is  and also received the Courage [[Teen Choice Award]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Silverman|first=Stephen M.|title=Lindsay Lohan Top Teen Choice Awards|url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,678707,00.html|work=People|accessdate=December 15, 2012|date=August 9, 2004}}</ref>\n\nIn 2004 MTV Books published Hamilton's book, ''Soul Surfer: A True Story of Faith, Family, and Fighting to Get Back on the Board'', which describes her ordeal. Her story is also told in the 2007 [[short subject]] [[documentary film]] ''Heart of a Soul Surfer''. Described as a \"faith-based documentary\", the film addresses her devout Christianity and the courage and faith in [[Jesus|Jesus Christ]] in the aftermath of the shark attack, and follows her quest for spiritual meaning.<ref>{{cite web|title=Heart of a Soul Surfer|publisher=Walking on Water|url=http://www.walkingonwater.org/films/heart_of_a_soul_surfer|accessdate=June 8, 2007|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070701105031/http://www.walkingonwater.org/films/heart_of_a_soul_surfer/|archivedate=July 1, 2007|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Heart of a Soul Surfer: The Bethany Hamilton Movie|url=http://www.heartofasoulsurfer.com|accessdate=June 8, 2007}}</ref>\n\nIn 2009 she was a contestant on ''[[Are You Smarter than a 5th Grader? (U.S. game show)|Are You Smarter Than a Fifth Grader?]]'' and won $25,000. In 2010 she appeared on an episode of ABC's ''[[Extreme Makeover: Home Edition]]''. \n\nIn 2011 Hamilton appeared in a video for the Christian organization [[I Am Second]], telling of her struggle after the shark attack and how she trusted in God to get her through it.{{fact|date=January 2020}} In 2011 a feature film ''[[Soul Surfer (film)|Soul Surfer]]'', based on her 2004 book, was released in theaters. Hamilton was portrayed by actress [[AnnaSophia Robb]]. Hamilton herself performed all the one-armed surfing stunts in it.<ref>{{cite web|last=Pilkington|first=Maria|title=Bethany Hamilton (Soul Surfer) Interview|url=http://thefourohfive.com/news/article/bethany-hamilton-soul-surfer-interview|work=The 405|accessdate=December 15, 2012|date=September 27, 2011}}</ref>\n\nShe also appeared on the TLC series ''[[19 Kids and Counting]]'' the same year, in the episode titled \"Duggars Under the Sea\", when the Duggar family visited her in [[Atlanta, Georgia]].{{fact|date=January 2020}}\n\nHamilton plays herself in the film ''[[Dolphin Tale 2]]'', which revolves around the baby dolphin Hope's story.<ref>{{cite web|title=Bethany Hamilton Appears in New 'Dolphin Tale 2'|url=http://www.christianpost.com/news/bethany-hamilton-appears-in-new-dolphin-tale-2-trailer-new-film-release-date-announced-video-121707|date=2014-06-17|accessdate=2014-08-24}}</ref> Hamilton and her husband, Adam Dirks, competed as a team on [[The Amazing Race 25|the 25th season]] of ''[[The Amazing Race (American TV series)|The Amazing Race]]'', finishing in third place. It premiered on 2014 on [[CBS]].<ref name=\"hitfix teams\">{{cite web|url=http://www.hitfix.com/the-fien-print/amazing-race-season-25-cast-features-survivor-veterans-surfer-bethany-hamilton|title=Cast features survivor veterans, surfer Bethany Hamilton|date=2014-05-31|accessdate=2014-05-31}}</ref>\n\n''Bethany Hamilton: Unstoppable'' is set to tell the story of her transition from childhood to motherhood. \"From chasing her toddler to chasing the biggest waves. Bethany is continuously re-writing the rules on being a fearless athlete, and brings a new meaning to the phrase, 'Surf Like a Girl'\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://bethanyhamilton.com/biography/|title=Bethany\u2019s Story|website=Bethany Hamilton|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-29}}</ref> {{New section}}\n\n== Books ==\nHamilton has published eight books with her Mom publishing one about her story. \n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+\n!Book Title\n!Authors\n!Year Published\n!Plot\n|-\n|Soul Surfer:A True Story of Faith, Family, and Fighting to Get Back on the Board\n|Bethany Hamilton, Rick Bundschuh, and Sheryl Berk\n|2004\n|Autobiography detailing the time leading up to the shark attack, how she recovered, dealt with media attention, and how she ultimately got back on the board and returned to competition\n|-\n|Devotions for the Soul Surfer\n|Bethany Hamilton \n|2006, reprinted in 2011\n|Christian devotional book for young girls \n|-\n|Rise Above: A 90 day Devotional \n|Bethany Hamilton\n|2007\n|Christian devotional for young girls discussing both \"hot and cool topics that every young girl faces\" <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://bethanyhamilton.com/|title=Bethany Hamilton {{!}} Soul Surfer, Professional Surfer, Role Model, Inspiration|website=Bethany Hamilton|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-29}}</ref>\n|-\n|Ask Bethany: FAQs: Surfing, Faith, and Friends\n|Bethany Hamilton \n|2007\n|Bethany answers questions discussing faith and how it has helped her throughout her life \n|-\n|Raising a Soul Surfer: One Family's Epic Tale \n|Cheri Hamilton, Rick Bundschuh\n|2011\n|This book was written by Hamilton's Mom and provides the story of Bethany's shark attack through the perspective of her parents. \n|-\n|Body and Soul: A Girl's Guide to a Fit, Fun, and Fabulous Life \n|Bethany Hamilton, Dustin Dillberg\n|2014\n|Provides readers with guidelines to become their healthiest self and practice a fit lifestyle. Includes workouts, healthy recipes, and tips for coping with stress<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://bethanyhamilton.com/|title=Bethany Hamilton {{!}} Soul Surfer, Professional Surfer, Role Model, Inspiration|website=Bethany Hamilton|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-29}}</ref>\n|-\n|Ask Bethany: Bethany Answers Over 200 Questions from Girls Like You\n|Bethany Hamilton, Doris Rikkers\n|2014, reprinted 2016\n|Bethany answers fan questions about \"a wide variety of topics about her life and faith\" <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://bethanyhamilton.com/|title=Bethany Hamilton {{!}} Soul Surfer, Professional Surfer, Role Model, Inspiration|website=Bethany Hamilton|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-29}}</ref>\n|-\n|Be Unstoppable: The Art of Never Giving Up\n|Bethany Hamilton\n|2018\n|In this book Bethany \"inspires readers to be bold, enjoy life, and take risk of trusting God each day. Includes photos, inspiration quotes, and life lessons from Hamilton <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://bethanyhamilton.com/|title=Bethany Hamilton {{!}} Soul Surfer, Professional Surfer, Role Model, Inspiration|website=Bethany Hamilton|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-29}}</ref>\n|-\n|Unstoppable Me\n|Bethany Hamilton, Adam Dirks, illustrated by Gill Guile\n|2018\n|Children's book based on Bethany's story. It follows Makana the lion who enjoys surfing but loses her nerve after wiping out on the water. With the help of her friends she rediscovers her love for surfing. <ref>{{Cite book|url=https://www.booksamillion.com/p/Unstoppable/Adam-Dirks/9780310764977|title=Unstoppable Me: Adam Dirks: 9780310764977|language=en}}</ref>\n|}\n\n== Outreach Programs ==\nHamilton is involved in numerous charitable efforts, including her own foundation, Friends of Bethany,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.friendsofbethany.com|title=Friends of Bethany Hamilton \u2013 A non-profit which reaches out to encourage a broken world offering hope to overcome through Jesus Christ|website=www.friendsofbethany.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-06-06}}</ref> which reaches out to amputees and youth, encouraging them to overcome difficulties by offering hope through Jesus Christ. Using her platform as a professional athlete to promote living a fit and healthy lifestyle, she authored the book ''Body and Soul'' in 2014. In 2019 a surf documentary was made about her, ''Bethany Hamilton: Unstoppable',<ref>[[imdbtitle:6435258|Bethany Hamilton: Unstoppable (2018)]] IMDb. Retrieved 14 July 2019.</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.unstoppablethefilm.net|title=BETHANY HAMILTON: UNSTOPPABLE|website=Unstoppable|language=en-US|access-date=2018-06-06}}</ref> which was accompanied by a photo book and a children's book.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://bethanyhamilton.com/unstoppablebooks|title=Bethany Hamilton {{!}}   Unstoppable Books|website=bethanyhamilton.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-06-06}}</ref>''\n\nWithin the Friends of Bethany Foundation there are four different programs:\n\n* Beautifully Flawed: retreat designed for young women ages 14-25 who have experienced traumatic limb loss. Six events hosted annually through this program which include: guests speakers, practical health and wellness tips which specifically account for limb loss, postural training, and surf lessons.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.friendsofbethany.com/|website=www.friendsofbethany.com|access-date=2020-02-29}}</ref>\n* Shine Forth: Night filled with stories and inspiration to overcome, free community event to gather together and share comeback stories. Bethany also does a book signing at this event, which is hosted annually.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.friendsofbethany.com/|website=www.friendsofbethany.com|access-date=2020-02-29}}</ref>\n* Anchored in Love: Conference for girls and young women ages 12 and up, one day event designed to help girls and young women discover their true beauty, purpose, and worth. Event is held annually in San Diego and features several guest speakers. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.friendsofbethany.com/|website=www.friendsofbethany.com|access-date=2020-02-29}}</ref>\n* The Forge: Men's retreat where young male amputees come and focus on faith, fitness, and healthy living. This program is run by Bethany, her husband, and friend/mentor Mike Coots.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.friendsofbethany.com/|website=www.friendsofbethany.com|access-date=2020-02-29}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|http://bethanyhamilton.com/}}\n* [http://www.cbsnews.com/stories/2004/12/30/earlyshow/leisure/books/main664024.shtml CBS News interview]\n* [http://www.makers.com/bethany-hamilton Bethany Hamilton] Video produced by ''[[Makers: Women Who Make America]]''\n* [http://www.theinertia.com/surf/red-water-bethany-hamilton-and-the-teeth-of-the-tiger/ Bethany Hamilton and the Teeth of the Tiger]\n* [https://surfergirls.com/bethany-hamilton/ Surfer Girls - Bethany Hamilton]\n* {{IMDb name|nm1703268}}\n{{ESPY Comeback Athlete}}\n{{The Amazing Race contestants}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hamilton, Bethany}}\n[[Category:1990 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:21st-century American non-fiction writers]]\n[[Category:21st-century American women]]\n[[Category:21st-century American women writers]]\n[[Category:21st-century Christians]]\n[[Category:The Amazing Race contestants]]\n[[Category:American amputees]]\n[[Category:American autobiographers]]\n[[Category:American disabled sportspeople]]\n[[Category:American surfers]]\n[[Category:Amputee sportspeople]]\n[[Category:Christians from Hawaii]]\n[[Category:American female surfers]]\n[[Category:People from Lihue, Hawaii]]\n[[Category:Shark attack victims]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Hawaii]]\n[[Category:Women autobiographers]]\n[[Category:Writers from Hawaii]]\n[[Category:American women non-fiction writers]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American surfer}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=August 2013}}\n{{Infobox surfer\n| name           = Bethany Hamilton\n| image          = Bethany Hamilton surfing (sq cropped).jpg\n| caption        = Hamilton surfing in September 2016\n| birth_name     = Bethany Meilani Hamilton\n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|mf=yes|1990|2|8}} \n| birth_place    = [[Lihue, Hawaii]], U.S.\n| residence      = [[Kauai, Hawaii]], U.S\n| height         = {{convert|5|ft|11|in|m|abbr=on}}\n| weight         = {{convert|155|lb|kg|abbr=on}}\n| best_year      = 2005 \n| sponsor's       = [[Rip Curl]]\n| major_achievements = [[ESPY Award]] (2004)<br />[[National Scholastic Surfing Association|NSSA]] National Helping Kids Champion (2005)<br />2nd place, [[Association of Surfing Professionals|ASP]] World Junior Championships (2008)\n| website         = {{url|bethanyhamilton.com}}\n| children        = 2\n}}\n\n'''Bethany Meilani Hamilton''' (born February 8, 1990) is an American professional [[surfing|surfer]] who survived a 2003 [[shark attack]] in which her left arm was bitten off but who ultimately returned to [[World Surf League|professional surfing]]. She wrote about her experience in the 2004 autobiography ''Soul Surfer: A True Story of Faith, Family, and Fighting to Get Back on the Board''. In April 2011, the feature film ''[[Soul Surfer (film)|Soul Surfer]]'' was released. She now has a new movie called ''Unstoppable'' where she shows the struggles and happiness of her family. Hamilton has been in the World Surf League for quite a few years.\n\n==Surfing career==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- style=\"background:lime green;\"\n! colspan=\"4;\"  style=\"background:green; color:white; text-align:center;\"| Placings in surf competitions\n|- style=\"background:#bdb76b;\"\n! Year!!Event!!Place!!Country\n|-\n| 1998 || Rell Sun Menehune || 1st|| [[Australia]]\n|-\n| 2002 || Open Women's Division of the [[National Scholastic Surfing Association|NSSA]] ||  1st || [[United States|USA]]\n|-\n| 2004 || NSSA National Competition ||  1st  || Australia\n|-\n| 2005 || NSSA National Competition ||  1st || USA\n|-\n| 2006 || NSSA National Championship: 18-and-under Finalist ||  5th  || USA\n|-\n| 2006 || Hawaii Team Highlights || 4th<br>3th* || USA\n|-\n| 2007 || NSSA Regionals || 1st  || USA\n|-\n| 2007 || T & C  Pipeline Women's Pro ||  1st  || USA\n|-\n| 2008 || US Open of Surfing\u2014[[Huntington Beach, California]] ||  5th  || USA\n|-\n| 2008 || Roxy Pro Surf Festival\u2014[[Phillip Island]] ||  3rd || Australia\n|-\n|2008\n|ASP's World Qualifying Series\n|14th\n|\n|-\n| 2009 || Rio Surf International in [[Rio de Janeiro]] ||  3rd  || [[Brazil]]\n|-\n|2009\n|WSL's World Qualifying Series \n|14th\n|Peru\n|-\n| 2009 || Billabong ASP World Junior Championship  ||  2nd || Australia\n|-\n|2012\n|Rip Curl Cup Padang Padang \n|\n|Indonesia\n|-\n| 2014 || Surf 'n' Sea Pipeline Women's Pro  ||  1st || USA\n|-\n| 2015 || Swatch Women's Pro<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldsurfleague.com/events/2015/wct/1282/swatch-womens-pro/results?resultsType=prizes|title=Prizes & Placing - 2015 Swatch Women's Pro|publisher=}}</ref>  ||  13th || USA \n|-\n| 2016 || Fiji Women's Pro<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldsurfleague.com/events/2016/wct/1440/fiji-womens-pro/results|title=Results - 2016 Fiji Women's Pro|publisher=}}</ref>  ||  3rd || [[Fiji]]\n|}\nShe was the first woman surfer to surf in the Rip Curl Cup in 2012.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://indosurflife.com/2012/07/bethany-hamilton-receives-wildcard-entry-into-rip-curl-padang-cup/|title=Bethany Hamilton receives wildcard entry into Rip Curl Padang Cup|date=2012-07-25|website=IndoSurfLife.com|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-29}}</ref> <!-- \n<nowiki>*</nowiki>4th at Brazil event, 5th at World Games event in the United States.\n-->\n\n==Personal life==\nHamilton was born on February 8, 1990 to Tom and Cheri Hamilton, on the day of a double rainbow.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://bethanyhamilton.com/|title=Bethany Hamilton {{!}} Soul Surfer, Professional Surfer, Role Model, Inspiration|website=Bethany Hamilton|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-29}}</ref> She has two older brothers Noah (born in 1981) and Timothy (born in 1986). She began surfing at the age of 8 and gained her first sponsorship by age 9.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.biography.com/athlete/bethany-hamilton|title=Bethany Hamilton|website=Biography|language=en-us|access-date=2020-02-29}}</ref> Hamilton was home-schooled from 6th grade through high school. She is a Christian.<ref name=\"home-school1\" /> In early 2012 Hamilton met youth minister<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20801085,00.html|title=Bethany Hamilton: My Husband Keeps Me Surfing|last=Dodd|first=Johnny|date=March 28, 2014|work=People|accessdate=March 28, 2014}}</ref> Adam Dirks through mutual friends.<ref name=\"us2013\">{{cite web|url=http://www.usmagazine.com/celebrity-news/news/pro-surfer-bethany-hamilton-marries-adam-dirks-2013188|title=Pro Surfer Bethany Hamilton Marries Adam Dirks|last=Webber|first=Stephanie|date=August 18, 2013|work=Us Weekly|accessdate=August 18, 2013}}</ref> They became engaged in 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.etonline.com/news/133768_Surfer_and_Shark_Attack_Survivor_Bethany_Hamilton_Engaged_to_Adam_Dirks/index.html|title=Surfer Bethany Hamilton Engaged|last=Wicks|first=Krista|date=May 7, 2013|work=Entertainment Tonight|accessdate=May 8, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.gospelherald.com/articles/48397/20130712/soul-surfer-bethany-hamilton-engaged-to-wed-youth-minister-adam-dirks.htm|title=Soul Surfer Bethany Hamilton Engaged to Wed Youth Minister Adam Dirks|date=12 July 2013}}</ref> The couple were married on August 18, 2013 at an estate on [[Kauai]]'s north shore, near where she grew up.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20727275,00.html|title=Bethany Hamilton's Official Wedding Photo|accessdate=June 22, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.gospelherald.com/articles/48646/20130818/soul-surfer-bethany-hamilton-gets-married-to-christian-youth-minister-adam-dirks.htm|title=Soul Surfer Bethany Hamilton Gets Married to Christian Youth Minister Adam Dirks|date=18 August 2013}}</ref> The couple have a son named Tobias, born in 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2015/06/15/bethany-hamilton-baby_n_7588512.html?ncid=txtlnkusaolp00000592|title=Bethany Hamilton Introduces New Baby Boy With Adorable Family Photo|last=Herreria|first=Carla|date=June 15, 2015|work=[[The Huffington Post]]|accessdate=June 15, 2015}}</ref> In 2018 they had a second son, Wesley.<ref>{{cite tweet|user=bethanyhamilton|author=Bethany Hamilton|number=917133168196460544|title=More than thankful to share our joyous news!!! #babyinthere #babyonboard\u2728\ud83c\udf89\u2764\ufe0f|date=October 8, 2017|accessdate=October 8, 2017}}</ref> She also has two shar pei dogs named Hanalei \"Hana\" and Kombucha \"Booch\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://bethanyhamilton.com/|title=Bethany Hamilton {{!}} Soul Surfer, Professional Surfer, Role Model, Inspiration|website=Bethany Hamilton|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-29}}</ref>\n\n==Shark attack and recovery==\nOn October 31, 2003, Hamilton, aged 13 at the time, went for a morning surf along Tunnels Beach, [[Kauai]], with her best friend [[Alana Blanchard]], Alana's father and brother, Holt and Byron, when a {{convert|14|ft|m|adj=mid|-long}} [[tiger shark]] attacked her,<ref>{{cite web |title=About |work=Bethany's General Biography |publisher=BethanyHamilton.com |year=2003 | url=http://www.bethanyhamilton.com/ |accessdate=September 17, 2007}}</ref> severing her left arm just below the shoulder. The Blanchards helped paddle her back to shore, then Alana's father fashioned a [[tourniquet]] out of a rash guard and wrapped it around the stump of her arm. She was rushed to [[Wilcox Health|Wilcox Memorial Hospital]]. By the time she arrived there she had lost over 60% of her blood and was in [[Hypovolemia|hypovolemic shock]]. A doctor living in a hotel nearby raced to the rescue. Her father, who was scheduled to have knee surgery that same morning, was already there, but she took his place in the operating room. During subsequent media interviews, she confirmed that she felt normal when she was bitten and did not feel much pain from the bite at the moment of the disaster, but felt numb on the way to the hospital.\n[[file:Bethany Hamilton 20070311.jpg|thumb|Hamilton surfing in March 2007]]\n\nWhen the news broke out of the shark attack, a family of fishermen led by Ralph Young presented to investigators photos of a {{convert|14|ft|m|adj=mid|-long}} tiger shark they had caught and killed about one mile from the attack site. It had surfboard debris in its mouth. When measurements of its mouth were compared with those of Hamilton's broken board, it matched. In late 2004, the police officially confirmed that it was the same one that had attacked her.\n\nDespite the trauma of the incident, Hamilton was determined to return to surfing.<ref name=\"home-school1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.home-school.com/Articles/soul-surfer.php|title=Homeschool World - Articles - Soul Survivor: The Bethany Hamilton Story - Practical Homeschooling Magazine|publisher=Home-school.com|date=2003-10-31|accessdate=2014-04-28}}</ref> One month after the attack, she returned to her board.<ref>{{cite web|last=Clark |first=Mark |title=Soul Surfer Interview With Bethany Hamilton! |url=http://whatculture.com/film/soul-surfer-interview-with-bethany-hamilton.php |work=WhatCulture! |accessdate=December 15, 2012 |date=September 24, 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131029204455/http://whatculture.com/film/soul-surfer-interview-with-bethany-hamilton.php |archivedate=October 29, 2013 |df=mdy }}</ref>\n\nInitially, she adopted a custom-made board that was longer and slightly thicker than standard and had a handle for her right arm, making it easier to paddle, and she learned to kick more to make up for the loss of her left arm. After teaching herself to surf with one arm, she returned to surfing on November 26, 2003, just 26 days after the attack and entered her first major competition on January 10, 2004.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://bethanyhamilton.com/|title=Bethany Hamilton {{!}} Soul Surfer, Professional Surfer, Role Model, Inspiration|website=Bethany Hamilton|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-29}}</ref> She now uses standard competitive performance short-boards.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://theinjuryco-op.com/bethany-hamilton-amputee-surfer/#.U17YSfldWT8 |title=Bethany Hamilton \u2013 Amputee Surfer &#124; The Injury Cooperative|publisher=Theinjuryco-op.com|accessdate=2014-04-28}}</ref> The shark-bitten surfboard that Hamilton was riding during the attack, as well as the bathing suit she was wearing at the time, a gift from ocean photographer [[Aaron Chang]], are on display at the [[California Surf Museum]] in [[Oceanside, California]].<ref>{{cite web|author=Guy Bagley|url=http://surfmuseum.org/surfmuseumexhibits.html|title=Current Exhibits|publisher=Surfmuseum.org|accessdate=August 19, 2013|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130806070345/http://surfmuseum.org/surfmuseumexhibits.html|archivedate=August 6, 2013|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"CSM\">Museum Exhibit (Permanent Exhibit). [http://surfmuseum.org/bethany-hamilton-courageous-inspiration/ \"Courageous Inspiration: Bethany Hamilton\"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160914180722/http://surfmuseum.org/bethany-hamilton-courageous-inspiration/ |date=September 14, 2016 }} ''California Surf Museum''. Retrieved 6 September 2016.</ref>\n\n==Media==\nSince the attack she has appeared as a guest on numerous television shows. Her manager, Roy \"Dutch\" Hofstetter, who went on to produce the film ''[[Soul Surfer (film)|Soul Surfer]]'', managed her rise through the media from shark attack victim to inspirational role model. The television shows she has appeared on include ''[[The Biggest Loser]]'', ''[[20/20 (U.S. TV series)|20/20]]'', ''[[Good Morning America]]'', ''[[Inside Edition]]'', ''[[The Oprah Winfrey Show]]'', ''[[The Ellen DeGeneres Show]]'', ''[[Today (U.S. TV program)|The Today Show]]'', ''[[The Tonight Show]]'' and ''[[Dude Perfect]]'', as well as in the magazines ''[[People (magazine)|People]]'', ''[[Time (magazine)|Time]]'', and ''[[American Girl (magazine)|American Girl]]''. Additionally she was the cover story in the first issue of ''[[NiNe. magazine|niNe]]'' magazine.<ref>[http://thegardenisland.com/news/article_15d110c8-4bc0-5459-b4db-dbd8c506752a.html \"Shark attack survivor discusses products and jewelry lines in new mag\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160411132331/http://thegardenisland.com/news/article_15d110c8-4bc0-5459-b4db-dbd8c506752a.html |date=April 11, 2016 }} by Lanaly Cabali, [http://thegardenisland.com The Garden Island], June 30, 2006.</ref>\n\nShe has participated in multiple public speaking events and is \"motivating audiences worldwide to live their life with more tenacity, courage, and faith\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://bethanyhamilton.com/|title=Bethany Hamilton {{!}} Soul Surfer, Professional Surfer, Role Model, Inspiration|website=Bethany Hamilton|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-29}}</ref>\n\nIn 2004 she won the [[ESPY Award]] for [[Best Comeback Athlete ESPY Award|Best Comeback Athlete]]<ref>{{cite web|title=The 2004 ESPY Awards winners|url=http://espn.go.com/espy2004/s/04nomineesindex.html|publisher=ESPN|accessdate=December 15, 2012}}</ref>is  and also received the Courage [[Teen Choice Award]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Silverman|first=Stephen M.|title=Lindsay Lohan Top Teen Choice Awards|url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,678707,00.html|work=People|accessdate=December 15, 2012|date=August 9, 2004}}</ref>\n\nIn 2004 MTV Books published Hamilton's book, ''Soul Surfer: A True Story of Faith, Family, and Fighting to Get Back on the Board'', which describes her ordeal. Her story is also told in the 2007 [[short subject]] [[documentary film]] ''Heart of a Soul Surfer''. Described as a \"faith-based documentary\", the film addresses her devout Christianity and the courage and faith in [[Jesus|Jesus Christ]] in the aftermath of the shark attack, and follows her quest for spiritual meaning.<ref>{{cite web|title=Heart of a Soul Surfer|publisher=Walking on Water|url=http://www.walkingonwater.org/films/heart_of_a_soul_surfer|accessdate=June 8, 2007|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070701105031/http://www.walkingonwater.org/films/heart_of_a_soul_surfer/|archivedate=July 1, 2007|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Heart of a Soul Surfer: The Bethany Hamilton Movie|url=http://www.heartofasoulsurfer.com|accessdate=June 8, 2007}}</ref>\n\nIn 2009 she was a contestant on ''[[Are You Smarter than a 5th Grader? (U.S. game show)|Are You Smarter Than a Fifth Grader?]]'' and won $25,000. In 2010 she appeared on an episode of ABC's ''[[Extreme Makeover: Home Edition]]''. \n\nIn 2011 Hamilton appeared in a video for the Christian organization [[I Am Second]], telling of her struggle after the shark attack and how she trusted in God to get her through it.{{fact|date=January 2020}} In 2011 a feature film ''[[Soul Surfer (film)|Soul Surfer]]'', based on her 2004 book, was released in theaters. Hamilton was portrayed by actress [[AnnaSophia Robb]]. Hamilton herself performed all the one-armed surfing stunts in it.<ref>{{cite web|last=Pilkington|first=Maria|title=Bethany Hamilton (Soul Surfer) Interview|url=http://thefourohfive.com/news/article/bethany-hamilton-soul-surfer-interview|work=The 405|accessdate=December 15, 2012|date=September 27, 2011}}</ref>\n\nShe also appeared on the TLC series ''[[19 Kids and Counting]]'' the same year, in the episode titled \"Duggars Under the Sea\", when the Duggar family visited her in [[Atlanta, Georgia]].{{fact|date=January 2020}}\n\nHamilton plays herself in the film ''[[Dolphin Tale 2]]'', which revolves around the baby dolphin Hope's story.<ref>{{cite web|title=Bethany Hamilton Appears in New 'Dolphin Tale 2'|url=http://www.christianpost.com/news/bethany-hamilton-appears-in-new-dolphin-tale-2-trailer-new-film-release-date-announced-video-121707|date=2014-06-17|accessdate=2014-08-24}}</ref> Hamilton and her husband, Adam Dirks, competed as a team on [[The Amazing Race 25|the 25th season]] of ''[[The Amazing Race (American TV series)|The Amazing Race]]'', finishing in third place. It premiered on 2014 on [[CBS]].<ref name=\"hitfix teams\">{{cite web|url=http://www.hitfix.com/the-fien-print/amazing-race-season-25-cast-features-survivor-veterans-surfer-bethany-hamilton|title=Cast features survivor veterans, surfer Bethany Hamilton|date=2014-05-31|accessdate=2014-05-31}}</ref>\n\n''Bethany Hamilton: Unstoppable'' is set to tell the story of her transition from childhood to motherhood. \"From chasing her toddler to chasing the biggest waves. Bethany is continuously re-writing the rules on being a fearless athlete, and brings a new meaning to the phrase, 'Surf Like a Girl'\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://bethanyhamilton.com/biography/|title=Bethany\u2019s Story|website=Bethany Hamilton|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-29}}</ref> {{New section}}\n\n== Books ==\nHamilton has published eight books with her Mom publishing one about her story. \n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+\n!Book Title\n!Authors\n!Year Published\n!Plot\n|-\n|Soul Surfer:A True Story of Faith, Family, and Fighting to Get Back on the Board\n|Bethany Hamilton, Rick Bundschuh, and Sheryl Berk\n|2004\n|Autobiography detailing the time leading up to the shark attack, how she recovered, dealt with media attention, and how she ultimately got back on the board and returned to competition\n|-\n|Devotions for the Soul Surfer\n|Bethany Hamilton \n|2006, reprinted in 2011\n|Christian devotional book for young girls \n|-\n|Rise Above: A 90 day Devotional \n|Bethany Hamilton\n|2007\n|Christian devotional for young girls discussing both \"hot and cool topics that every young girl faces\" <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://bethanyhamilton.com/|title=Bethany Hamilton {{!}} Soul Surfer, Professional Surfer, Role Model, Inspiration|website=Bethany Hamilton|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-29}}</ref>\n|-\n|Ask Bethany: FAQs: Surfing, Faith, and Friends\n|Bethany Hamilton \n|2007\n|Bethany answers questions discussing faith and how it has helped her throughout her life \n|-\n|Raising a Soul Surfer: One Family's Epic Tale \n|Cheri Hamilton, Rick Bundschuh\n|2011\n|This book was written by Hamilton's Mom and provides the story of Bethany's shark attack through the perspective of her parents. \n|-\n|Body and Soul: A Girl's Guide to a Fit, Fun, and Fabulous Life \n|Bethany Hamilton, Dustin Dillberg\n|2014\n|Provides readers with guidelines to become their healthiest self and practice a fit lifestyle. Includes workouts, healthy recipes, and tips for coping with stress<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://bethanyhamilton.com/|title=Bethany Hamilton {{!}} Soul Surfer, Professional Surfer, Role Model, Inspiration|website=Bethany Hamilton|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-29}}</ref>\n|-\n|Ask Bethany: Bethany Answers Over 200 Questions from Girls Like You\n|Bethany Hamilton, Doris Rikkers\n|2014, reprinted 2016\n|Bethany answers fan questions about \"a wide variety of topics about her life and faith\" <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://bethanyhamilton.com/|title=Bethany Hamilton {{!}} Soul Surfer, Professional Surfer, Role Model, Inspiration|website=Bethany Hamilton|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-29}}</ref>\n|-\n|Be Unstoppable: The Art of Never Giving Up\n|Bethany Hamilton\n|2018\n|In this book Bethany \"inspires readers to be bold, enjoy life, and take risk of trusting God each day. Includes photos, inspiration quotes, and life lessons from Hamilton <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://bethanyhamilton.com/|title=Bethany Hamilton {{!}} Soul Surfer, Professional Surfer, Role Model, Inspiration|website=Bethany Hamilton|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-29}}</ref>\n|-\n|Unstoppable Me\n|Bethany Hamilton, Adam Dirks, illustrated by Gill Guile\n|2018\n|Children's book based on Bethany's story. It follows Makana the lion who enjoys surfing but loses her nerve after wiping out on the water. With the help of her friends she rediscovers her love for surfing. <ref>{{Cite book|url=https://www.booksamillion.com/p/Unstoppable/Adam-Dirks/9780310764977|title=Unstoppable Me: Adam Dirks: 9780310764977|language=en}}</ref>\n|}\n\n== Outreach Programs ==\nHamilton is involved in numerous charitable efforts, including her own foundation, Friends of Bethany,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.friendsofbethany.com|title=Friends of Bethany Hamilton \u2013 A non-profit which reaches out to encourage a broken world offering hope to overcome through Jesus Christ|website=www.friendsofbethany.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-06-06}}</ref> which reaches out to amputees and youth, encouraging them to overcome difficulties by offering hope through Jesus Christ. Using her platform as a professional athlete to promote living a fit and healthy lifestyle, she authored the book ''Body and Soul'' in 2014. In 2019 a surf documentary was made about her, ''Bethany Hamilton: Unstoppable',<ref>[[imdbtitle:6435258|Bethany Hamilton: Unstoppable (2018)]] IMDb. Retrieved 14 July 2019.</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.unstoppablethefilm.net|title=BETHANY HAMILTON: UNSTOPPABLE|website=Unstoppable|language=en-US|access-date=2018-06-06}}</ref> which was accompanied by a photo book and a children's book.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://bethanyhamilton.com/unstoppablebooks|title=Bethany Hamilton {{!}}   Unstoppable Books|website=bethanyhamilton.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-06-06}}</ref>''\n\nWithin the Friends of Bethany Foundation there are four different programs:\n\n* Beautifully Flawed: retreat designed for young women ages 14-25 who have experienced traumatic limb loss. Six events hosted annually through this program which include: guests speakers, practical health and wellness tips which specifically account for limb loss, postural training, and surf lessons.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.friendsofbethany.com/|website=www.friendsofbethany.com|access-date=2020-02-29}}</ref>\n* Shine Forth: Night filled with stories and inspiration to overcome, free community event to gather together and share comeback stories. Bethany also does a book signing at this event, which is hosted annually.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.friendsofbethany.com/|website=www.friendsofbethany.com|access-date=2020-02-29}}</ref>\n* Anchored in Love: Conference for girls and young women ages 12 and up, one day event designed to help girls and young women discover their true beauty, purpose, and worth. Event is held annually in San Diego and features several guest speakers. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.friendsofbethany.com/|website=www.friendsofbethany.com|access-date=2020-02-29}}</ref>\n* The Forge: Men's retreat for young males amputees come and focus on faith, fitness, and healthy living. This program is run by Bethany, her husband, and friend/mentor Mike Coots.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.friendsofbethany.com/|website=www.friendsofbethany.com|access-date=2020-02-29}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|http://bethanyhamilton.com/}}\n* [http://www.cbsnews.com/stories/2004/12/30/earlyshow/leisure/books/main664024.shtml CBS News interview]\n* [http://www.makers.com/bethany-hamilton Bethany Hamilton] Video produced by ''[[Makers: Women Who Make America]]''\n* [http://www.theinertia.com/surf/red-water-bethany-hamilton-and-the-teeth-of-the-tiger/ Bethany Hamilton and the Teeth of the Tiger]\n* [https://surfergirls.com/bethany-hamilton/ Surfer Girls - Bethany Hamilton]\n* {{IMDb name|nm1703268}}\n{{ESPY Comeback Athlete}}\n{{The Amazing Race contestants}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hamilton, Bethany}}\n[[Category:1990 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:21st-century American non-fiction writers]]\n[[Category:21st-century American women]]\n[[Category:21st-century American women writers]]\n[[Category:21st-century Christians]]\n[[Category:The Amazing Race contestants]]\n[[Category:American amputees]]\n[[Category:American autobiographers]]\n[[Category:American disabled sportspeople]]\n[[Category:American surfers]]\n[[Category:Amputee sportspeople]]\n[[Category:Christians from Hawaii]]\n[[Category:American female surfers]]\n[[Category:People from Lihue, Hawaii]]\n[[Category:Shark attack victims]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Hawaii]]\n[[Category:Women autobiographers]]\n[[Category:Writers from Hawaii]]\n[[Category:American women non-fiction writers]]\n", "name_user": "MilesOdonnol", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eOutreach Programs:minor grammar edits. No change to meaning.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bethany_Hamilton"}
